      ]
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "This function should be called in two places, when an IP address is added and when the hardware address changes. This function will setup the ifaddr_t for use with the IP ARP functions. This function will also trigger the transmission of a gratuitous ARP packet.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "When the SIOCSIFADDR ioctl is handled, the data parameter will be an ifaddr_t. If this is an IP address, inet_arp_init_ifaddr should be called. This is usually performed in the protocol attachment's ioctl handler.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "When the event handler for the protocol attachment receives a KEV_DL_LINK_ADDRESS_CHANGED event, the event handler should call inet_arp_init_ifaddr for each interface ip address.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "For an example, see bsd/net/ether_inet_pr_module.c in xnu. Search for inet_arp_init_ifaddr.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
